[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-13T20:21:04+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/l1bh8k08T5dFkhWLhftrpu2efvk=/535x0:2323x1192/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73459217/Screenshot_2024_07_13_at_3.08.10_PM.0.png\" />\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"pab02r\">There\u2019s a bit of a theme of payoff in this week\u2019s trailers. Anthony Mackie finally takes the lead on the big screen after 10 years in the MCU; Ridley Scott\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.ign.com/articles/2003/09/11/ridley-talks-gladiator-2\">two-decade-plus plan</a> for a <em>Gladiator</em> sequel is coming to fruition; and we finally get to find out what happens next to the macrodata refinement team in <em>Severance. </em></p>\n<p id=\"U4TmD4\">There\u2019s a lot to go through this week, from big-budget tentpole movies to whimsical TV, so let\u2019s get down to it, starting, naturally, with the MCU.</p>\n<h2 id=\"6uTEqg\"><em>Captain America: Brave New World</em></h2>\n<div id=\"PWhaAq\"><div style=\"width: 100%; height: 0; padding-bottom: 56.25%;\"></div></div>\n<p id=\"", "id": 860419, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/13/24197907/trailers-week-july-8-13-captain-america-brave-new-world-gladiator-ii-f1-time-bandits-severance", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Trailers of the week: Captain America, F1, and Gladiator II", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-13T14:39:03+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The new Kobo Elipsa 2E on a desk surrounded by papers.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com